Sentinel v0.9.5.109

Summary:
- Add local glyph target gating before Character ReOCR.
- Keep Joncollins-style 2/z and 1/l targets and case-sensitive alliance tag targets.
- Skip broad non-local Unicode/UNKNOWN drift so the validator does not waste OCR or imply solvable glyph proof where none exists.
- Add character_reocr_skipped_nonlocal to reports.
- Update docs and version metadata.

Validation:
pytest -q tests/smoke/test_glyph_verification_109.py tests/smoke/test_targeted_character_reocr_geometry_106.py tests/smoke/test_character_reocr_debug_102.py
python -m py_compile ground_truth_validator.py parser/targeted_character_reocr.py

Commit command:
git add .
git commit -m "feat(data-guard): gate reocr to local glyph verification"

Tag command:
git tag -a v0.9.5.109 -m "v0.9.5.109 Glyph Verification Engine Gate"
